today i went to my step cousins birthday party. shes one of those fake nice people, i see the bitch in her. her bf is some homeboy whose hella nice. i didnt see them touch or sit or talk together. cute? i played some mean games of volleyball.
[[[[[i love my boyfriend, even when hes not around i have so much more confidence. ive become so much more outgoing. gaaaaaaah. i can see his "good morning" face everywhere i go. in those silly purple soccer pants. and i know youre reading this, so tell me you love me, punk. haha]]]]]

my parents are in hawaii til next wednesday.
he told me not to go home tonite, but i didnt wanna stay up all night by myself and wake up early for him to leave and for me to lay there all day by myself. but being here alone sucks more, i shoulda stayed with him. i always miss sleeping next to him, but when im there sometimes my insomnia kicks in. i wish it was still summer so he could spend all week with me.
i remember the first 4 days we spent together, with no parents. they were so much fun. we learned so much about each other. we fell in love that week.
why do they call it FALLING in love? falling is usually seen as a bad thing, but i guess love turns out bad 9 outta 10 times. tho it wasnt love if it ends up bad...i talk in circles.
he played with my necklace like he was some sort of fucking cat, god it doesnt get any more cute then that.

then we saw wicker park. and the movie was fuckin sweet. the way it was filmed was cool and you couldnt figure the movie out no matter how hard you try. although i realized josh harnett looks way too much like my brother.

the mall was closed on our way out, we were the only ones walkin thru and we talked and talked and laughed and laughed. we proceeded to kiss in the rain: and i can definitely say that he stood (at my door) with his hands on my waiste and kissed me like he ment it, and i knew, that he ment it. i spent the nite at his house and  (as sara would say) we did the things that boyfriends and girlfriends do when no ones around. he made me mashed potatoes too.

today laurren and i went shopping in georgetown. the town was really pretty minus the dirty water. its so weird seeing people walking across or down the street, you never saw that in cow county. i will admit, i love the country life. i spent 8 million dollars and i really shouldnt have. but whatever, my dad bribs me with his money and it works. haha

i fell in love all over again this weekend. i got that feeling in my chest when he kissed me, everytime.

everything he does is the cutest thing ive ever seen. ive never seen anyone so beautiful, inside and out.

friday: marc's band (theres always forever) had a show at st johns with underscore, bury me standing, silent film, and derby lane. very good lineup i must say. everyone loved marc's band and it was fucking cute. there was an out of line reunion. lillian and i got to talk. patti and i had a deep talk. kristin and emma made the car ride enjoyable. my boyfriend fucking rocked your socks on that stage, although london made fun of him, but it was cute. glassjaw greg might just be one of my favorite people. matt and i hugged. afterwards i slept at marcys house and we fell asleep so fast.

saturday: woke up at marc's after he had left for work. went to cow county to see my tisha. we did some good bonding, weve been friends since 3rd grade, dont mess. then i picked up marc from work and we came back to my house to have funfun sleepy time. there was a huge spiderweb going across the walkway to my door, and a huge spider in it. i was a real man and tore that sucker down while marc stood there scared. HELLS YEAH! he insisted on drying my hair and styling it. he didnt steal the blanket or push me off the bed this time. we watched the girl next door and he held me like he was a part of me. we kissed the night away and i fell asleep happier then ever.
